definitions: To guide or manipulate (a vehicle, aircraft, etc.) with skill.
To perform a movement or series of moves requiring skill and care.
To skillfully plan and direct a situation or person.
examples: She had to maneuver the car into a tight parking spot.
The pilot will maneuver the plane through the storm.
He tried to maneuver his way out of the difficult conversation.
The general will maneuver his troops into position.
